<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3328] Extend client JDBC object factory with methods to create objects required for statement pooling</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3328</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since statement pooling introduces new types of objects, the factories must be extended to handle these new types.&lt;br/&gt;
This step is primarily required because we support multiple versions of the JDBC standard, which in turn implies running with different interfaces and JVM versions with differing features.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
